        <name>on_capture_completed</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback is invoked when capturing single frame is completed and result is available. For MRCapture null metadata handle. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">result_metadata_handle</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Represents camera result metadata which could be used as input handle for camera result metadata related functions. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">extra</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Carries capture result information of current captured frame. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Custom data to be returned when callback is triggered. This data passed in <ref refid="group___camera_1gac97ec7063117126c48d9d3bcb5258822" kindref="member">MLCameraSetCaptureCallbacks</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
